# Cloud-Agnostic FinOps AI Platform — Revised Architecture

## Design Principles

1. **No cloud-specific storage** — PostgreSQL, not S3/Athena
2. **No cloud-specific compute** — APScheduler, not Lambda
3. **Multi-cloud connectors** — each tool supports AWS + Azure + GCP
4. **FOCUS as the universal language** — all billing normalized before storage

---

## Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "Cloud Billing Sources"
        AWS["☁️ AWS CUR 2.0"]
        AZ["🔷 Azure Cost Mgmt"]
        GCP["🟡 GCP BigQuery Export"]
    end

    subgraph "Collectors (Python)"
        C1["aws_collector.py"]
        C2["azure_collector.py"]
        C3["gcp_collector.py"]
    end

    subgraph "FOCUS Normalizer"
        NORM["focus_normalizer.py<br/>All clouds → one schema"]
    end

    subgraph "Centralized Store (Cloud-Agnostic)"
        PG["🐘 PostgreSQL<br/>focus_billing table<br/>Runs ANYWHERE"]
    end

    subgraph "Spike Detector (In-Process)"
        SCHED["⏰ APScheduler<br/>(runs inside FastAPI)"]
    end

    subgraph "Multi-Cloud Connectors"
        OC["OpenCost<br/>Any K8s"]
        IC["Infracost<br/>Any Terraform"]
        CC["Cloud Custodian<br/>c7n / c7n-azure / c7n-gcp"]
    end

    subgraph "AI Agent Chain"
        RCA["🔍 RCA"] --> TAG["🏷️ Tags"]
        TAG --> FCST["📈 Forecast"]
        FCST --> ACT["⚡ Actions"]
    end

    AWS --> C1 --> NORM
    AZ --> C2 --> NORM
    GCP --> C3 --> NORM
    NORM --> PG
    PG --> SCHED
    SCHED -->|spike found| RCA
    PG --> RCA
    OC --> RCA
    IC --> RCA
    CC --> ACT
```

---

## Why PostgreSQL, Not S3

| Criteria | S3 + Athena | PostgreSQL |
|---|---|---|
| Runs on AWS only? | ✅ Yes (vendor lock-in) | ❌ Runs anywhere |
| Managed options | Only AWS | AWS RDS, Azure Database, GCP Cloud SQL, Supabase, self-hosted |
| Self-hostable | ❌ | ✅ Docker, K8s, bare metal |
| Query language | SQL (Athena-specific) | Standard SQL |
| Real-time queries | ~5s startup lag | Instant (<50ms) |
| Schema enforcement | Glue Crawler (AWS) | Native DDL |
| Cost at FinOps scale | $5/TB scanned | Free (self-hosted) or ~$15/mo managed |

> [!TIP]
> A year of billing data for 3 clouds with resource-level detail is typically **1-10M rows** — PostgreSQL handles this trivially with proper indexing. No need for a data lake.

---

## Phase 1: FOCUS Schema & PostgreSQL

### FOCUS Table Schema

```sql
CREATE TABLE focus_billing (
    id              BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    -- FOCUS core columns
    provider        VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,   -- AWS | Azure | GCP
    billing_period_start TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    billing_period_end   TIMESTAMP,
    billed_cost     DECIMAL(12,4) NOT NULL,
    effective_cost  DECIMAL(12,4),
    billing_currency VARCHAR(3) DEFAULT 'USD',
    -- Resource identification
    service_name    VARCHAR(255),
    service_category VARCHAR(255),
    resource_id     VARCHAR(512),
    resource_name   VARCHAR(255),
    resource_type   VARCHAR(255),
    region          VARCHAR(100),
    availability_zone VARCHAR(100),
    -- Account hierarchy
    billing_account_id   VARCHAR(255),
    billing_account_name VARCHAR(255),
    sub_account_id       VARCHAR(255),
    sub_account_name     VARCHAR(255),
    -- Tags (JSONB for flexible key-value pairs)
    tags            JSONB DEFAULT '{}',
    -- Usage
    usage_quantity  DECIMAL(18,6),
    usage_unit      VARCHAR(50),
    pricing_quantity DECIMAL(18,6),
    pricing_unit    VARCHAR(50),
    -- Metadata
    charge_type     VARCHAR(50),  -- Usage | Purchase | Tax | Credit
    ingested_at     TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),

    -- Indexes for common queries
    CONSTRAINT valid_provider CHECK (provider IN ('AWS', 'Azure', 'GCP'))
);

-- Performance indexes
CREATE INDEX idx_billing_period ON focus_billing(billing_period_start);
CREATE INDEX idx_provider ON focus_billing(provider);
CREATE INDEX idx_service ON focus_billing(service_name);
CREATE INDEX idx_resource ON focus_billing(resource_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_tags ON focus_billing USING GIN(tags);
```

### Docker Compose Addition

```yaml
services:
  postgres:
    image: postgres:16-alpine
    environment:
      POSTGRES_DB: finops
      POSTGRES_USER: finops
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: finops_secret
    ports: ["5432:5432"]
    volumes: ["pgdata:/var/lib/postgresql/data"]

volumes:
  pgdata:
```

