## Phase 4: Multi-Cloud Connectors

### 4.1 OpenCost — Already Cloud-Agnostic ✅

OpenCost runs on **any Kubernetes cluster** (EKS, AKS, GKE, self-hosted):

```bash
# AWS EKS
helm install opencost opencost/opencost -n opencost --create-namespace

# Azure AKS
helm install opencost opencost/opencost -n opencost --create-namespace \
  --set opencost.exporter.defaultClusterId=aks-cluster

# GCP GKE
helm install opencost opencost/opencost -n opencost --create-namespace \
  --set opencost.exporter.defaultClusterId=gke-cluster
```

**No code change needed** — same API (`/allocation`, `/assets`) regardless of cloud.

### 4.2 Infracost — Already Cloud-Agnostic ✅

Infracost works with **any Terraform provider**:

```bash
# AWS resources
infracost breakdown --path ./terraform/aws --format json

# Azure resources
infracost breakdown --path ./terraform/azure --format json

# GCP resources
infracost breakdown --path ./terraform/gcp --format json
```

**No code change needed** — same CLI, same JSON output format.

### 4.3 Cloud Custodian — Needs Multi-Cloud Packages

```bash
# Install per-cloud packages
pip install c7n          # AWS
pip install c7n-azure    # Azure
pip install c7n-gcp      # GCP
```

**Code change needed:** Update [cloud_custodian.py](file:///Users/utkarsh/Documents/Agents/finops-ai-platform/backend/app/connectors/cloud_custodian.py) to detect provider and use correct runner:

```python
# app/connectors/cloud_custodian.py (updated)

async def run_policy(policy_path: str, provider: str, dry_run: bool = True):
    if provider == "AWS":
        cmd = ["custodian", "run", "--dry-run" if dry_run else "", "-s", output_dir, policy_path]
    elif provider == "Azure":
        cmd = ["custodian", "run", "--dry-run" if dry_run else "", "-s", output_dir,
               "--provider", "azure", policy_path]
    elif provider == "GCP":
        cmd = ["custodian", "run", "--dry-run" if dry_run else "", "-s", output_dir,
               "--provider", "gcp", policy_path]
```

**Per-cloud policy directories:**
```
custodian-policies/
├── aws/
│   ├── unused-ebs.yml
│   └── idle-ec2.yml
├── azure/
│   ├── unused-disks.yml
│   └── idle-vms.yml
└── gcp/
    ├── unused-disks.yml
    └── idle-instances.yml
```

